            'title': 'hackerspaces.org (HSO) Yearly Meetup',
            'subtitle': null,
            'language': 'en',
            'track': null,
            'type': 'other',
            'abstract': '',
            'description': 'Created in 2008, the [hackerspaces.org](https://hackerspaces.org) website was a vital part of the growth of the hackerspace movement. It keeps being a great resource for creatures & communities wanting to start, operate, or just find information on hackspaces. Primarily a [wiki](https://wiki.hackerspaces.org/)\r\n, it allows anyone, anywhere in the world, to add their hackspace. The pages attract curious search traffic, open days visitors, and new members. They are also the backbone of regional and international hackspace interaction, including a [world map](https://wiki.hackerspaces.org/List_of_Hacker_Spaces), [mailing list](https://lists.hackerspaces.org/listinfo/discuss), [chatroom](https://wiki.hackerspaces.org/Communication), and [hacker residences](https://wiki.hackerspaces.org/Residencies) for travelling hackers.\r\n\r\nThe yearly CCC meetings help us keep the lights up, and to think of how to update & improve the site, keeping it relevant for the years to come.\r\nLet\'s get together, brainstorm, and discuss how to do this.\r\n\r\n# TIME & LOCATION TENTATIVE\r\n# CONFIRMED BY DEC 25\r\n# SEE IRC/[MATRIX](https://matrix.to/#/#chat:hackspaces.org) CHANNEL :)',
            'persons': [],
