              'name': 'Ren\u00e9 Walendy',
              'avatar_url': null,
              'biography': 'I\'m a PhD candidate at the Embedded Security Group at the Max Planck Institute for Security and Privacy and the SecHuman graduate school of Ruhr University Bochum, Germany. My research focuses on the human factors in hardware reverse engineering, and how we can make hardware security education accessible to more people. I also like to do low-level technical work on, for example, image processing algorithms for visual analysis of microchips.',
